&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 4 Data Results Management and Booking Coordinator&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Integrated Sexual Health and HIV service at BHRUT is currently seeking a motivated team player to take up the position of Data, Results Management &amp; Booking Co-ordinator. The candidate will support the service, focusing on operational performance and delivery. This is a busy and dynamic service where we put patients at the centre of the care that we provide. The successful candidate will require excellent communication, organisational skills and possess a positive can-do attitude.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Excellent IT skills including Microsoft Word, Excel and PowerPoint will be an essential for this role. A Microsoft Excel Test will be part of the interview process to assess skills required for the post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The service provides over 20,000 Genitourinary Medicine appointments and 12,000 contraception appointments each year. The service is interlinked with the HIV service provided from Barking Community Hospital, which as a patient cohort of c.950. Many staff within the ISHS and the HIV service work across all service elements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Pre coronavirus pandemic the service operated from four sites, with Barking Community Hospital as the main hub site operating 6 days per week, a Havering provision at Queen’s Hospital open three days per week and a Redbridge provision at Hainault Health Centre &amp; Loxford Polyclinic open one day per week at each site. This role will be predominantly based at Barking Community Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you believe you have the skills we require for this dynamic and transformational role, please apply now!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Informal enquiries should be addressed to: Gary Bradshaw by e-mail gary.bradshaw1@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All new staff appointed to posts at the Trust is subject to a probationary period. This will give the new staff member an opportunity to become familiar with the culture and working environment of the Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications should be made online, however, queries regarding the application process or assistance with completion of the form (for applicants with a disability) can be made to HR Recruitment Advisor Nadeem Arif, on 01708 435000 ext. 2289. Further details regarding the post may be obtained by contacting the manager as per the contact details above.&lt;/p&gt;
